In terms of bulk measures, each partition coefficient Kp (see Eq. 10.36) also equals the porosity ϕ times the bulk particulate concentration Cp (mg/m3 bulk) divided by the product of the dissolved (mg/l bulk) and particulate (mg/m3 bulk) bulk concentrations, CdCs, all times 106 mg/kg.10.54Kp=106ϕCp/(CdCs)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
